A former Bhisho legislature employee who was fired for alleging some senior administration bosses at the institution were having sex with juniors and interns in exchange for promotions, is demanding the release of the legislature s sex for jobs investigation report. Dismissed legislature whistleblower Luzuko Kerr Hoho, outed author of the once-anonymous Father Punch newsletter, last week wrote to the institution demanding that the report be publicly released.For the full story get a copy of the Dispatch or subscribe to our e-Edition for the complete newspaper with jobs, classifieds, crosswords, TV schedules and back editions